WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.313 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.313 --> 00:00:07.245 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.245 --> 00:00:10.150 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.150 --> 00:00:13.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Have you noticed, whenever
you see a commercial for ham

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:19.430 align:middle line:84%
on TV, it's often set in the
countryside with a nice family

00:00:19.430 --> 00:00:22.150 align:middle line:90%
and a rustic backdrop.

00:00:22.150 --> 00:00:29.520 align:middle line:84%
And the ham is always pink,
very pink, and 100% natural,

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:30.495 align:middle line:90%
of course.

00:00:30.495 --> 00:00:32.970 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:00:32.970 --> 00:00:35.820 align:middle line:84%
>> It looks so tasty, it
has your mouth watering

00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:37.802 align:middle line:90%
on the couch.

00:00:37.802 --> 00:00:38.760 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's the point.

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:43.360 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:46.770 align:middle line:84%
But what if behind this pretty
pink hid one of the biggest

00:00:46.770 --> 00:00:49.710 align:middle line:90%
health scandals of our era?

00:00:49.710 --> 00:00:52.380 align:middle line:84%
In 2015, the World
Health Organization

00:00:52.380 --> 00:00:55.420 align:middle line:84%
listed processed meats
as carcinogenic for man.

00:00:55.420 --> 00:00:58.680 align:middle line:90%


00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:01.320 align:middle line:84%
We decided to investigate
the ingredients used

00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:03.400 align:middle line:84%
by the giants of
the food industry.

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:08.430 align:middle line:84%
>> It can induce DNA breaks,
mutate cells into sort

00:01:08.430 --> 00:01:11.100 align:middle line:90%
of pre-cancer cells.

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:14.130 align:middle line:84%
>> We discovered that to impede
or halt regulations on certain

00:01:14.130 --> 00:01:16.710 align:middle line:84%
additives, food industry
lobbies have been working

00:01:16.710 --> 00:01:19.875 align:middle line:90%
in the shadows for decades.

00:01:19.875 --> 00:01:23.700 align:middle line:84%
>> You have to understand that
the industry is a money-making

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:26.220 align:middle line:84%
business, so they're
very risk averse.

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:28.980 align:middle line:84%
They're not going
to fund a study that

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:30.790 align:middle line:90%
is bad for their business.

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:38.770 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:42.040 align:middle line:84%
>> At the heart of this strategy
of influence are the scientists

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:43.260 align:middle line:90%
who collaborate--

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:46.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Did the meat industry
pay you for this?

00:01:46.420 --> 00:01:48.880 align:middle line:84%
>> I received some
compensation for my time,

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:50.470 align:middle line:90%
as well as the others.

00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:51.940 align:middle line:90%
>> How much?

00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:55.190 align:middle line:90%
>> I am not going to say.

00:01:55.190 --> 00:01:58.050 align:middle line:84%
>> --and the scientists
who are targeted.

00:01:58.050 --> 00:02:01.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Basically they're trying to
shoot me down or discredit me.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:04.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what shoot
down means, scientifically.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:06.140 align:middle line:90%
[BEEPING]

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:10.280 align:middle line:84%
>> These efforts to go after
the scientists and to discredit

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:14.540 align:middle line:84%
the scientists is a key element
of a much larger strategy

00:02:14.540 --> 00:02:19.470 align:middle line:84%
to just gum up the entire
policymaking process.

00:02:19.470 --> 00:02:22.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Between intimidation,
lies, and manipulation,

00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:25.560 align:middle line:84%
we will uncover proof of
a worldwide strategy where

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:28.226 align:middle line:84%
hitting below the
belt is allowed.

00:02:28.226 --> 00:02:29.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Leave now.

00:02:29.410 --> 00:02:31.230 align:middle line:90%
Get the fuck out of here.

00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:32.130 align:middle line:90%
[DOOR SLAMS]

00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:33.030 align:middle line:90%


00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:34.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Feeling hungry now?

00:02:34.530 --> 00:02:36.120 align:middle line:90%
Then it's time to eat.

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:37.855 align:middle line:90%
Tonight, you are our guest.

00:02:37.855 --> 00:02:40.430 align:middle line:90%


00:02:40.430 --> 00:02:44.760 align:middle line:84%
To find out how ham is
made, we visited a factory.

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:48.632 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:02:48.632 --> 00:02:49.604 align:middle line:90%
[BEEPING]

00:02:49.604 --> 00:02:51.550 align:middle line:90%


00:02:51.550 --> 00:02:55.030 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to Fleury Michon, one
of the market leaders in France

00:02:55.030 --> 00:02:57.460 align:middle line:84%
and one of the few to play
the card of transparency.

00:02:57.460 --> 00:02:59.790 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:02:59.790 --> 00:03:01.510 align:middle line:84%
The ham on your
supermarket shelves

00:03:01.510 --> 00:03:04.880 align:middle line:84%
starts out like this,
big lumps of pork meat.

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:10.520 align:middle line:90%


00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:12.620 align:middle line:84%
To add taste, a little
vegetable stock.

00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:15.330 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:18.190 align:middle line:84%
It all goes into a ham-shaped
mold, and it's cooked.

00:03:18.190 --> 00:03:21.860 align:middle line:90%


00:03:21.860 --> 00:03:26.100 align:middle line:84%
And the result, perfectly
pink, rounded slices.

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:27.960 align:middle line:90%
Have you grasped the basics?

00:03:27.960 --> 00:03:30.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's rewind a little
to see the detail that

00:03:30.330 --> 00:03:33.700 align:middle line:90%
changes everything.

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:37.130 align:middle line:84%
To obtain this fine ham, there's
another very important step.

00:03:37.130 --> 00:03:41.220 align:middle line:90%


00:03:41.220 --> 00:03:42.780 align:middle line:90%
You have to inject the meat.

00:03:42.780 --> 00:03:45.900 align:middle line:90%


00:03:45.900 --> 00:03:49.800 align:middle line:84%
A machine with a dozen
syringes injects a liquid

00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:51.370 align:middle line:90%
into the lumps of pork meat.

00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:58.480 align:middle line:90%


00:03:58.480 --> 00:04:01.540 align:middle line:84%
The liquid contains
an essential additive.

00:04:01.540 --> 00:04:06.060 align:middle line:84%
Factory manager Laurent
Rouleau shows us.

00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:09.060 align:middle line:84%
These yellow sacks contain
a mixture of salt and sodium

00:04:09.060 --> 00:04:14.962 align:middle line:90%
nitrite, the additive E250.

00:04:14.962 --> 00:04:34.680 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:04:34.680 --> 00:04:37.460 align:middle line:84%
>> In fact, he's telling us
that the pretty pink of our ham

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:38.600 align:middle line:90%
isn't natural at all.

00:04:38.600 --> 00:04:42.030 align:middle line:90%


00:04:42.030 --> 00:04:45.460 align:middle line:90%
It's thanks to sodium nitrite.

00:04:45.460 --> 00:04:49.620 align:middle line:84%
This additive fixes the pink
of the meat during cooking.

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, ham would be
the color of roast pork.

00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:54.900 align:middle line:90%


00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:56.940 align:middle line:84%
That's why food
industrialists can't

00:04:56.940 --> 00:05:01.680 align:middle line:84%
do without it, as a processed
meats producer would confirm.

00:05:01.680 --> 00:05:02.770 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:05:02.770 --> 00:05:40.020 align:middle line:90%


00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:41.130 align:middle line:90%
Let's sum up.

00:05:41.130 --> 00:05:44.100 align:middle line:84%
The ham's pink is unnatural,
but without the pink

00:05:44.100 --> 00:05:45.570 align:middle line:90%
it would be impossible to sell.

00:05:45.570 --> 00:05:48.288 align:middle line:90%


00:05:48.288 --> 00:05:49.200 align:middle line:90%
[BEEPING]

00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:51.120 align:middle line:84%
The big problem is
that sodium nitrite

00:05:51.120 --> 00:05:53.250 align:middle line:84%
is believed to be a
danger to public health.

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:57.140 align:middle line:90%


00:05:57.140 --> 00:05:59.600 align:middle line:84%
The additive is suspected
of playing a role

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:06.140 align:middle line:84%
in the development of colorectal
cancer, one of the deadliest

00:06:06.140 --> 00:06:07.310 align:middle line:90%
cancers in Europe.

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:10.962 align:middle line:90%


00:06:10.962 --> 00:06:14.630 align:middle line:84%
The cause, a phenomenon that
takes place during digestion.

00:06:14.630 --> 00:06:18.490 align:middle line:90%


00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:21.210 align:middle line:84%
It's chemistry, but
we'll make it simple.

00:06:21.210 --> 00:06:24.190 align:middle line:84%
You swallow a piece
of cured meat.

00:06:24.190 --> 00:06:26.440 align:middle line:84%
You think you're
peacefully digesting it,

00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:28.480 align:middle line:84%
but what you don't
know is the nitrite

00:06:28.480 --> 00:06:31.180 align:middle line:84%
molecules are reacting
with the meat proteins,

00:06:31.180 --> 00:06:35.940 align:middle line:84%
transforming them into
very dangerous substances,

00:06:35.940 --> 00:06:36.960 align:middle line:90%
nitrosamines.

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:42.290 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.290 --> 00:06:43.990 align:middle line:84%
We went to the
Netherlands to learn more

00:06:43.990 --> 00:06:46.030 align:middle line:84%
about the effects of
this chemical reaction

00:06:46.030 --> 00:06:50.070 align:middle line:84%
on our health, to the
faculty of medicine

00:06:50.070 --> 00:06:51.787 align:middle line:90%
of Maastricht University.

00:06:51.787 --> 00:06:54.530 align:middle line:90%


00:06:54.530 --> 00:06:59.420 align:middle line:84%
This is where the toxicologist
professor Théo de Kok works.

00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:01.670 align:middle line:84%
He's been interested
in nitrites for years

00:07:01.670 --> 00:07:03.900 align:middle line:90%
and by extension, nitrosamines.

00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:06.980 align:middle line:90%


00:07:06.980 --> 00:07:10.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Nitrosamines are known to
induce damage in the large

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:10.800 align:middle line:90%
intestine.

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:14.900 align:middle line:84%
So it can induce DNA
breaks, mutate cells

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:17.780 align:middle line:90%
into sort of pre-cancer cells.

00:07:17.780 --> 00:07:21.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's, of course, something
that you want to prevent.

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:24.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Professor de Kok notably
wanted to find out what happens

00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:28.370 align:middle line:84%
inside the body when we don't
eat processed meat and when we

00:07:28.370 --> 00:07:29.900 align:middle line:90%
eat a lot of it.

00:07:29.900 --> 00:07:32.120 align:middle line:84%
To do so, he conducted
an experiment

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:33.860 align:middle line:84%
with human guinea
pigs, like Arnaud.

00:07:33.860 --> 00:07:37.010 align:middle line:90%


00:07:37.010 --> 00:07:39.530 align:middle line:84%
For two weeks, this
student ate 300 grams

00:07:39.530 --> 00:07:42.530 align:middle line:84%
of processed meat a day, the
equivalent of eight and 1/2

00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:45.090 align:middle line:90%
sausages or seven slices of ham.

00:07:45.090 --> 00:07:47.930 align:middle line:90%


00:07:47.930 --> 00:07:52.280 align:middle line:84%
>> After 15 days, we saw that
the exposure to nitrosamines

00:07:52.280 --> 00:07:56.600 align:middle line:84%
was considerably increased,
so it was up to between two

00:07:56.600 --> 00:07:59.720 align:middle line:84%
and three-fold increase, as
compared to the levels that we

00:07:59.720 --> 00:08:02.260 align:middle line:90%
measured at the start.

00:08:02.260 --> 00:08:04.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The researcher measured the
impact on the organism of this

00:08:04.990 --> 00:08:08.200 align:middle line:84%
chemical mutation of
nitrites into nitrosamines.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:11.730 align:middle line:90%


00:08:11.730 --> 00:08:15.180 align:middle line:84%
In his lab, he tested the fecal
water of big processed meat

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:16.260 align:middle line:90%
eaters like Arnaud.

00:08:16.260 --> 00:08:23.540 align:middle line:90%


00:08:23.540 --> 00:08:27.680 align:middle line:84%
>> So what you see here is
fecal water from four different

00:08:27.680 --> 00:08:30.420 align:middle line:90%
individuals.

00:08:30.420 --> 00:08:32.520 align:middle line:84%
>> To see what happens
inside the body,

00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:37.700 align:middle line:84%
the researchers mixed this
fecal water with human cells,

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:41.630 align:middle line:84%
the white deposit
in the test tube.

00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:46.020 align:middle line:84%
Then they observed what
happened to the cells.

00:08:46.020 --> 00:08:47.940 align:middle line:84%
>> So you see that if
you have no exposure,

00:08:47.940 --> 00:08:49.600 align:middle line:84%
you see that
everything is intact.

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:51.220 align:middle line:90%
So the material stays together.

00:08:51.220 --> 00:08:55.080 align:middle line:84%
But if you are exposed
to nitrosamines

00:08:55.080 --> 00:08:58.180 align:middle line:84%
that induce
breakages of the DNA,

00:08:58.180 --> 00:09:00.310 align:middle line:84%
you see this comet
tail appearing.

00:09:00.310 --> 00:09:03.030 align:middle line:84%
So you see that here, the
damage is quite extensive.

00:09:03.030 --> 00:09:05.760 align:middle line:84%
So the more damage you
have, the more likely

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:09.330 align:middle line:84%
it is that a cell like
this will eventually mutate

00:09:09.330 --> 00:09:11.790 align:middle line:90%
into a pre-cancer type of cell.

00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:15.170 align:middle line:84%
>> How long does it
take for such a damage?

00:09:15.170 --> 00:09:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, this damage can be
induced relatively quickly.

00:09:17.740 --> 00:09:20.250 align:middle line:84%
So in this assay, when
we isolate the cells--

00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:22.710 align:middle line:84%
and we only expose
them for half an hour--

00:09:22.710 --> 00:09:26.730 align:middle line:84%
and then you already see the
breakage of these DNA strands.

00:09:26.730 --> 00:09:28.900 align:middle line:90%
That's how fast it can happen.

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And it can also happen not
just in the lab here, but also

00:09:32.190 --> 00:09:33.480 align:middle line:90%
in an intact human body.

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:36.050 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:39.240 align:middle line:84%
>> And if we stop using
nitrites, then what?

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:42.230 align:middle line:84%
>> That would make a difference
of potentially several

00:09:42.230 --> 00:09:47.010 align:middle line:84%
thousands of colorectal cancer
that's in Europe every year.

00:09:47.010 --> 00:09:48.050 align:middle line:90%
>> That's huge?

00:09:48.050 --> 00:09:49.370 align:middle line:90%
>> That's huge.

00:09:49.370 --> 00:09:54.560 align:middle line:84%
Because colorectal cancer
is a very frequent disease.

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:57.650 align:middle line:84%
Already small changes
in cancer risk

00:09:57.650 --> 00:10:02.281 align:middle line:84%
can have a big impact
in the large population.

00:10:02.281 --> 00:10:05.050 align:middle line:90%


00:10:05.050 --> 00:10:08.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Thousands fewer cancers and
therefore potentially fewer

00:10:08.380 --> 00:10:10.780 align:middle line:84%
deaths just by
suppressing nitrites.

00:10:10.780 --> 00:10:17.120 align:middle line:90%


00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:19.640 align:middle line:84%
But the food industry has
a sledgehammer argument

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:22.227 align:middle line:84%
for justifying the
use of nitrites.

00:10:22.227 --> 00:10:23.435 align:middle line:90%
It protects us from botulism.

00:10:23.435 --> 00:10:27.110 align:middle line:90%


00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:29.510 align:middle line:84%
Botulism is a form of
food poisoning caused

00:10:29.510 --> 00:10:32.120 align:middle line:84%
by bacteria that affect
our central nervous system

00:10:32.120 --> 00:10:34.310 align:middle line:90%
and can be deadly.

00:10:34.310 --> 00:10:37.200 align:middle line:90%
Scary, right?

00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:38.825 align:middle line:84%
But there's a glitch
in their argument.

00:10:38.825 --> 00:10:42.740 align:middle line:90%


00:10:42.740 --> 00:10:44.140 align:middle line:84%
There are already
companies which

00:10:44.140 --> 00:10:47.170 align:middle line:84%
do produce processed
meats without nitrites,

00:10:47.170 --> 00:10:49.210 align:middle line:84%
and their customers
are in fine form.

00:10:49.210 --> 00:11:00.810 align:middle line:90%


00:11:00.810 --> 00:11:03.690 align:middle line:84%
If you happen to be in
Copenhagen in Denmark,

00:11:03.690 --> 00:11:07.020 align:middle line:84%
just after the Little Mermaid
and the quayside promenade,

00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:11.510 align:middle line:84%
pop into a supermarket
like we did.

00:11:11.510 --> 00:11:14.330 align:middle line:84%
There, you'll find cured
meats without nitrites.

00:11:14.330 --> 00:11:17.060 align:middle line:90%


00:11:17.060 --> 00:11:19.630 align:middle line:84%
And for those whose Danish
has gone a bit rusty,

00:11:19.630 --> 00:11:23.230 align:middle line:90%
it's uden nitrit.

00:11:23.230 --> 00:11:26.450 align:middle line:90%
It's everywhere.

00:11:26.450 --> 00:11:28.880 align:middle line:84%
You can easily recognize
it by its color,

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:30.620 align:middle line:90%
more brownish than pretty pink.

00:11:30.620 --> 00:11:34.000 align:middle line:90%


00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And the best known brand is
produced 150 kilometers south

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:41.530 align:middle line:84%
of the capital in Denmark's
biggest organic processed meat

00:11:41.530 --> 00:11:42.960 align:middle line:90%
plant, Hanegal.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:46.412 align:middle line:90%


00:11:46.412 --> 00:11:49.120 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:52.780 align:middle line:84%
>> The boss, a biochemist,
started in nitrite-free cured

00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:54.230 align:middle line:90%
meats 25 years ago.

00:11:54.230 --> 00:11:57.890 align:middle line:90%


00:11:57.890 --> 00:11:59.950 align:middle line:84%
Since then, the Danish
health authorities

00:11:59.950 --> 00:12:02.680 align:middle line:84%
haven't registered a
single case of botulism

00:12:02.680 --> 00:12:06.240 align:middle line:90%
caused by processed meat.

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:09.780 align:middle line:84%
>> We do not have problems
with this bacteria.

00:12:09.780 --> 00:12:12.240 align:middle line:84%
I would say for
the last 50 years,

00:12:12.240 --> 00:12:18.560 align:middle line:84%
this has not been a reasonable
topic in Western Europe.

00:12:18.560 --> 00:12:23.330 align:middle line:84%
That was a problem in meat
industry 100 years ago,

00:12:23.330 --> 00:12:26.570 align:middle line:84%
where things were not
as clean as they are.

00:12:26.570 --> 00:12:29.730 align:middle line:84%
Slaughterhouses were not
as clean as they are today.

00:12:29.730 --> 00:12:32.880 align:middle line:90%
So no worry about bacteria.

00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:35.000 align:middle line:84%
Now we have to worry
about additives

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:38.000 align:middle line:90%
that might be cancer producing.

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:40.880 align:middle line:84%
And if they are not necessary
for some very good reasons,

00:12:40.880 --> 00:12:42.290 align:middle line:90%
we should not use them.

00:12:42.290 --> 00:12:45.070 align:middle line:84%
