overlooking the capital,

00:18:22.740 --> 00:18:26.280 align:middle line:84%
its president, Richard
Lyng, spoke out.

00:18:26.280 --> 00:18:32.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Processed meats that contain
nitrites are a big thing.

00:18:32.080 --> 00:18:37.030 align:middle line:84%
The retail value of them,
about $12.5 billion.

00:18:37.030 --> 00:18:41.230 align:middle line:84%
About 2/3 of the hog
production in the United States

00:18:41.230 --> 00:18:43.270 align:middle line:90%
goes into cured meats.

00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:46.960 align:middle line:84%
And it presents a
problem for our industry

00:18:46.960 --> 00:18:49.570 align:middle line:90%
and for the government.

00:18:49.570 --> 00:18:54.490 align:middle line:84%
We're hopeful that a
solution can be found.

00:18:54.490 --> 00:18:56.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Armed with
financial analysis,

00:18:56.380 --> 00:19:00.070 align:middle line:84%
the American meat lobby forced
the government to back down.

00:19:00.070 --> 00:19:03.340 align:middle line:84%
The banning of nitrites would
