hot dogs now and cancer.

00:20:17.220 --> 00:20:19.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Put yourself in the shoes
of the average American Joe

00:20:19.920 --> 00:20:22.950 align:middle line:90%
at the time.

00:20:22.950 --> 00:20:26.040 align:middle line:84%
You and your family are eating
hot dogs at the shopping mall

00:20:26.040 --> 00:20:27.660 align:middle line:90%
or in the street just as usual.

00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:30.480 align:middle line:90%


00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:32.580 align:middle line:90%
The effect was immediate.

00:20:32.580 --> 00:20:37.750 align:middle line:84%
In a matter of days, hot
dog sales fell by 8%.

00:20:37.750 --> 00:20:40.060 align:middle line:84%
And given the size of
the American market,

00:20:40.060 --> 00:20:41.890 align:middle line:84%
that represented
millions of dollars

00:20:41.890 --> 00:20:43.300 align:middle line:90%
less for the food industry.

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:50.920 align:middle line:90%


00:20:50.920 --> 00:20:54.370 align:middle line:84%
The author of the hot dog study
that caused sales to plummet

00:20:54.370 --> 00:20:57.900 align:middle line:90%
was Susan Preston-Martin.

00:20:57.900 --> 00:20:59.720 align:middle line:84%
