00:24:41.120 --> 00:24:46.740 align:middle line:84%
we headed to northern
California, to San Francisco.

00:24:46.740 --> 00:24:51.750 align:middle line:90%


00:24:51.750 --> 00:24:54.180 align:middle line:84%
This university library
holds what are commonly

00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:58.590 align:middle line:84%
known as the Tobacco Documents,
millions of internal tobacco

00:24:58.590 --> 00:24:59.670 align:middle line:90%
industry documents.

00:24:59.670 --> 00:25:05.970 align:middle line:90%


00:25:05.970 --> 00:25:09.060 align:middle line:84%
Our guide, Stanton
Glantz, has spent his life

00:25:09.060 --> 00:25:11.760 align:middle line:84%
unraveling the cigarette
makers' strategies.

00:25:11.760 --> 00:25:14.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Carton four.

00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:17.940 align:middle line:84%
>> He particularly remembers
one phrase used by a lobbyist

00:25:17.940 --> 00:25:22.350 align:middle line:90%
in 1969.

00:25:22.350 --> 00:25:25.080 align:middle line:84%
>> "Doubt is our product
since it is the best means

00:25:25.080 --> 00:25:28.890 align:middle line:84%
of competing with the body of
fact that exists in the mind

00:25:28.890 --> 00:25:30.960 align:middle line:90%
of the general public.

00:25:30.960 --> 00:25:34.440 align:middle line:84%
It is also the means of
establishing a controversy."

00:25:34.440 --> 00:25:37.820 align:middle line:84%
>> For him, everything is
summed up in one word, doubt.

00:25:37.820 --> 00:25:42.100 align:middle line:90%


00:25:42.100 --> 00:25:45.060 align:middle line:84%
And it was exactly like
that, by creating doubt,

00:25:45.060 --> 00:25:48.030 align:middle line:84%
that Philip Morris set out to
discredit Dr. Preston-Martin's

00:25:48.030 --> 00:25:50.850 align:middle line:84%
study on processed meat
and cancer in children.

00:25:50.850 --> 00:25:54.700 align:middle line:90%


00:25:54.700 --> 00:25:57.280 align:middle line:84%
The proof is there
in the vast database

00:25:57.280 --> 00:25:58.690 align:middle line:90%
of the Tobacco Documents.

00:25:58.690 --> 00:26:02.680 align:middle line:90%


00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:07.810 align:middle line:84%
By typing Susan Preston-Martin,
you get hundreds of hits

00:26:07.810 --> 00:26:09.750 align:middle line:84%
and all in the
Philip Morris file.

00:26:09.750 --> 00:26:14.550 align:middle line:90%


00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:16.540 align:middle line:84%
The researcher's name
crops up regularly

00:26:16.540 --> 00:26:19.930 align:middle line:84%
in the titles of memos,
letters, and internal reports.

00:26:19.930 --> 00:26:23.140 align:middle line:90%


00:26:23.140 --> 00:26:26.010 align:middle line:84%
The multinational believed
her study on hot dogs

00:26:26.010 --> 00:26:28.260 align:middle line:84%
would reopen the debate
surrounding nitrites

00:26:28.260 --> 00:26:29.950 align:middle line:90%
from the 1970s.

00:26:29.950 --> 00:26:32.250 align:middle line:84%
So it paid scientists
to go through her work

00:26:32.250 --> 00:26:35.610 align:middle line:84%
with a fine tooth comb in
order to find any weak points.

00:26:35.610 --> 00:26:40.070 align:middle line:90%


00:26:40.070 --> 00:26:42.110 align:middle line:84%
Even her contracts
and grant papers

00:26:42.110 --> 00:26:48.650 align:middle line:84%
passed under the microscope,
basically anything that

00:26:48.650 --> 00:26:50.840 align:middle line:84%
could be used against
her and weaken her

00:26:50.840 --> 00:26:52.775 align:middle line:84%
in the eyes of the
government and the press.

00:26:52.775 --> 00:26:58.800 align:middle line:90%


00:26:58.800 --> 00:27:01.140 align:middle line:84%
Stanton Glantz only
learned of this case

00:27:01.140 --> 00:27:03.930 align:middle line:84%
through the documents
we showed him.

00:27:03.930 --> 00:27:07.280 align:middle line:84%
>> The approaches that they
used to attack the person doing

00:27:07.280 --> 00:27:11.180 align:middle line:84%
the research on linking
cured meats with cancer were

00:27:11.180 --> 00:27:12.560 align:middle line:90%
the standard things they do.

00:27:12.560 --> 00:27:16.730 align:middle line:84%
One is to go through her
work with a fine tooth comb

00:27:16.730 --> 00:27:20.540 align:middle line:84%
and find every little thing they
can possibly complain about.

00:27:20.540 --> 00:27:24.380 align:middle line:84%
And because the issues tend
to be fairly technical,

00:27:24.380 --> 00:27:27.080 align:middle line:84%
if you're a politician,
if you're a reporter,

00:27:27.080 --> 00:27:29.330 align:middle line:84%
unless you're a highly
specialized reporter,

00:27:29.330 --> 00:27:31.040 align:middle line:84%
all you hear is,
well, this person

00:27:31.040 --> 00:27:33.770 align:middle line:84%
said there was something
bad, and this other person

00:27:33.770 --> 00:27:36.300 align:middle line:84%
said they didn't know what
they were talking about.

00:27:36.300 --> 00:27:40.040 align:middle line:84%
And so these efforts to
go after the scientists

00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and to discredit the
scientists is a key element

00:27:43.370 --> 00:27:45.590 align:middle line:84%
of a much larger
strategy to just

00:27:45.590 --> 00:27:49.880 align:middle line:84%
gum up the entire policymaking
process to the point where

00:27:49.880 --> 00:27:51.530 align:middle line:90%
nothing happens.

00:27:51.530 --> 00:27:54.800 align:middle line:84%
That translates into hundreds
of billions of dollars

00:27:54.800 --> 00:27:56.780 align:middle line:90%
of sales and profits for them.

00:27:56.780 --> 00:28:03.810 align:middle line:84%
So the whole game
is just slow down.

00:28:03.810 --> 00:28:06.330 align:middle line:84%
>> In the documents
on Dr. Preston-Martin,

00:28:06.330 --> 00:28:11.360 align:middle line:84%
other even more Machiavellian
scenarios were studied.

00:28:11.360 --> 00:28:12.980 align:middle line:84%
Here, it was
suggested that talks

00:28:12.980 --> 00:28:18.020 align:middle line:84%
be held with the scientist,
and here, a proposed seminar

00:28:18.020 --> 00:28:20.770 align:middle line:90%
in order to lure her.

00:28:20.770 --> 00:28:23.240 align:middle line:84%
The aim, to influence
her and even

00:28:23.240 --> 00:28:25.250 align:middle line:84%
shape the conclusions
of her future studies.

00:28:25.250 --> 00:28:30.730 align:middle line:90%


00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:32.810 align:middle line:84%
The common point
of these documents,

00:28:32.810 --> 00:28:36.800 align:middle line:84%
they all come from the same
lobbying firm, Multinational

00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:41.570 align:middle line:84%
Business Services, Inc.,
already hired by Philip Morris

00:28:41.570 --> 00:28:44.780 align:middle line:84%
to contest the effects of
passive smoking on health

00:28:44.780 --> 00:28:48.740 align:middle line:84%
and headed by a certain Jim
Tozzi, a master of influence.

00:28:48.740 --> 00:28:59.530 align:middle line:90%


00:28:59.530 --> 00:29:02.980 align:middle line:84%
Amazingly, in Washington,
the heart of American power,

00:29:02.980 --> 00:29:07.110 align:middle line:84%
this lobbyist is still
well established.

00:29:07.110 --> 00:29:09.750 align:middle line:84%
As he never answered our
requests for an interview,

00:29:09.750 --> 00:29:12.660 align:middle line:84%
we went to see him without an
appointment with our documents

00:29:12.660 --> 00:29:14.290 align:middle line:90%
in hand and a hidden camera.

00:29:14.290 --> 00:29:18.144 align:middle line:90%


00:29:18.144 --> 00:29:21.650 align:middle line:90%
[DOORBELL RINGS]

00:29:21.650 --> 00:29:22.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:29:22.450 --> 00:29:22.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello.

