>> Hello.

00:29:24.374 --> 00:29:26.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm looking for a Mr. Jim Tozzi.

00:29:26.730 --> 00:29:28.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, he works here.

00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:29.140 align:middle line:90%
Who are you with?

00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:31.140 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm a French journalist.

00:29:31.140 --> 00:29:32.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm working for France 2.

00:29:32.810 --> 00:29:35.360 align:middle line:90%
And I'm working on lobbying.

00:29:35.360 --> 00:29:37.300 align:middle line:84%
>> But do you have
an appointment?

00:29:37.300 --> 00:29:38.100 align:middle line:90%
>> No, no.

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:41.590 align:middle line:84%
I was just looking for him
because I called from friends.

00:29:41.590 --> 00:29:42.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Just step inside, please.

00:29:42.810 --> 00:29:43.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:29:43.610 --> 00:29:45.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Because he's not here now.

00:29:45.630 --> 00:29:49.770 align:middle line:84%
>> The good news, American
lobbyists can be welcoming.

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:52.680 align:middle line:84%
We even managed to have Jim
Tozzi on his cell phone.

00:29:52.680 --> 00:29:54.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Here, please.

00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:57.270 align:middle line:84%
Here, come on, right
in here, please.

00:29:57.270 --> 00:29:59.640 align:middle line:90%
Jim, can you hear me?

00:29:59.640 --> 00:30:01.930 align:middle line:84%
>> (ON PHONE) I
can hear you, yeah.

00:30:01.930 --> 00:30:04.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I wanted to ask you
some questions about Susan

00:30:04.590 --> 00:30:06.230 align:middle line:90%
Preston-Martin.

00:30:06.230 --> 00:30:08.310 align:middle line:84%
>> (ON PHONE) No, I
don't even know the lady.

00:30:08.310 --> 00:30:09.310 align:middle line:90%
How did you get my name?

00:30:09.310 --> 00:30:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I haven't read her
work or anything.

00:30:11.670 --> 00:30:15.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Because you have set up a
strategy to discredit her work

00:30:15.960 --> 00:30:17.700 align:middle line:90%
for Oscar Mayer.

00:30:17.700 --> 00:30:20.484 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to know
more about this.

00:30:20.484 --> 00:30:22.300 align:middle line:90%
>> (ON PHONE) [INAUDIBLE]

00:30:22.300 --> 00:30:24.020 align:middle line:90%
>> What?

00:30:24.020 --> 00:30:24.820 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me?

00:30:24.820 --> 00:30:28.010 align:middle line:90%


00:30:28.010 --> 00:30:32.130 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea what
she's talking about.

00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:33.960 align:middle line:84%
>> (ON PHONE) Is
this the press lady?

00:30:33.960 --> 00:30:35.070 align:middle line:90%
Which newspaper is she--

00:30:35.070 --> 00:30:37.380 align:middle line:84%
>> I have no idea who you're
working for, so I'm going

00:30:37.380 --> 00:30:38.095 align:middle line:90%
to ask you to leave.

00:30:38.095 --> 00:30:38.250 align:middle line:90%
>> I can send you my email.

00:30:38.250 --> 00:30:38.470 align:middle line:90%
No, no.

00:30:38.470 --> 00:30:39.330 align:middle line:90%
I can send you my email.

00:30:39.330 --> 00:30:39.390 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:30:39.390 --> 00:30:40.973 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

00:30:40.973 --> 00:30:42.181 align:middle line:90%
>> You have seen my passport.

00:30:42.181 --> 00:30:43.556 align:middle line:84%
I'm just asking
for an interview.

00:30:43.556 --> 00:30:44.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Look, I understand.

00:30:44.670 --> 00:30:46.350 align:middle line:84%
>> If you liked the
welcoming lobbyist,

00:30:46.350 --> 00:30:47.445 align:middle line:90%
you'll love the angry one.

00:30:47.445 --> 00:30:49.300 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm asking you-- you
have no appointment.

00:30:49.300 --> 00:30:50.610 align:middle line:90%
Now please leave, now.

00:30:50.610 --> 00:30:51.870 align:middle line:90%
Do I need to--

00:30:51.870 --> 00:30:52.710 align:middle line:90%
leave.

00:30:52.710 --> 00:30:53.550 align:middle line:90%
>> We can leave if we want?

00:30:53.550 --> 00:30:54.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, please leave.

00:30:54.580 --> 00:30:55.840 align:middle line:90%
I am ordering you out.

00:30:55.840 --> 00:30:56.640 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:30:56.640 --> 00:30:58.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Leave now.

00:30:58.380 --> 00:30:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Out.

00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:01.440 align:middle line:90%
Get the fuck out of here.

00:31:01.440 --> 00:31:02.375 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, OK, no problem.

00:31:02.375 --> 00:31:04.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you understand
get the fuck out?

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:10.350 align:middle line:84%
Now get the flying fuck out
of here, and do not come back.

00:31:10.350 --> 00:31:11.303 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:31:11.303 --> 00:31:12.189 align:middle line:90%
